(f) review every two years or as the need arises the Municipal Solid Waste Management Plan for the purpose of ensuring its sustainability, viability, effectiveness and relevance in relation to local and international developments in the field of solid waste management; 

(g) provide support to the concerned barangay for the construction of secured fence for the MRF for security, health and sanitation purposes; and  

(h) implement the plan of issuing Citation Tickets for violators of the Municipal Environmental Code to strengthen the drive for a more aggressive solid waste management program.

