d.	follow the new COA Circular 2020-006 re: Guidelines and Procedures in the Conduct of Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (PPE), Recognition of PPE Items Found at Station, and Disposition for Non-existing/Missing PPE Items, for the One-Time Cleansing of PPE Account Balances of Government Agencies to come up with reliable PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive instruct its officers and personnel to improve compliance in property accounting and custodianship controls which may include:

a.	reconstituting an Inventory Committee to include each Department Head to facilitate inventory-taking by Office of all the property, plant and equipment of the Municipality;

b.	preparing the updated Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) in the prescribed form as shown in Annex 49 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume II and submit the same to the auditor;                     

c.	requiring the Municipal Accountant and Property Custodian to record and keep track of all movements in the PPE and conduct periodic reconciliation of the accounting and property records;

d.	creating an appraisal committee for the unrecognized parcels of land to arrive at the fair value thereof to pave the way for their recognition in the books; and

e.	requiring the municipal officials concerned to ascertain the status of parcels of land owned by the Municipality with titling issues and work for the titling thereof in the name of the Municipality of Porac, assuming funds have been provided therefor.

We recommended that the Management

a. through the Liga ng mga Barangay, encourage active participation of barangay officials to support the solid waste management program of the government by educating their respective constituents on the proper segregation of reusable or recyclable materials from compostable wastes;



b. through the ESMO, comply with the requirements of the law on waste segregation by placing trash bins with proper labels and by collecting only those garbage that are properly segregated;



c. ensure that all barangays had existing and operational MRF;



d. recommend to the Sangguniang Bayan (SB) policies and possible measures that will ensure full compliance by the barangays on the provisions of R.A. No. 9003;




e. initiate the implementation of its Anti-Littering policy ordinances as provided by Section 48 thereof;




f. review every two years or as the need arises the Municipal Solid Waste Management Plan for the purpose of ensuring its sustainability, viability, effectiveness and relevance in relation to local and international developments in the field of solid waste management;




g. provide support to the concerned barangay for the construction of secured fence for the MRF for security, health and sanitation purposes; and 


h. implement the plan of issuing Citation Tickets in CY 2020 for violators of the Municipal Environmental Code to strengthen the drive for a more aggressive solid waste management program.

We recommended that the Management:

a.	comply with the aforementioned rules and regulations in the hiring of JOs and prepare and issue policies and guidelines to address the issue on the necessity and propriety of hiring JOs;



b.	strengthen the controls in the hiring of job order personnel by requiring them to submit personal records, undergo interview and document the evaluation of performance to give assurance that the risk identified above are addressed;

c.	prepare contract of service instead of job order sheet and incorporate therein the number of man hours, quantity and duration of the works and the list of duties and responsibilities to be performed;

d.	assess and review the necessity of hiring job orders by considering the existence of regular employees who could perform some of the contracted work and maximize the services of the regular employees and minimize the hiring of JOs;

e.	submit explanation for the deployment job order/contract of service personnel performing services to places other than the agency’s official workplace; and

f.	direct the municipal accountant to support disbursement of funds for services rendered by contract of service/job order personnel with the necessary and appropriate supporting documents to establish validity and proprietary of payment such as accomplishment report and the like.

