We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the:

(a)	Local School Board to (i) come up with a strategic prioritization plan in the allocation of the SEF to public schools taking into consideration the most important needs of the students and not just for repairs of school facilities for optimum attainment of the intent of the fund in accordance with DepEd-DDBM-DLG JC 2017-001; 

(b)	Municipal Engineering Office to conduct site inspection prior to the preparation of program of work and plans and specifications; and field monitoring on the progress and development of the projects to ensure compliance with the required technical specifications;

(c)	BAC Members, its Secretariat and GSO to improve  compliance to the  Revised IRR of RA 9184 IRR, particularly, Sections 10 and 48.2 regarding conduct of public bidding on procurement of goods and services exceeding P200,000.00, and Section 54.1 by avoiding splitting to avail of the least possible costs on procured goods and services, thus preventing overpricing and sanctions for violation of the procurement law and with the GPPB Resolution No. 09-2009 by posting in the Municipality and PhilGEPS websites the RFQ, PO/WO and Approved Budget for the Contract (ABC) of items to be procured to attract more bidders/suppliers and ensure competitiveness in the conduct of alternative modes of procurement.  The awards of contract to winning suppliers should also be posted to provide information on items with the lowest price in the market;

(d)	Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to submit to the LSB a certified statement of the actual income and expenditures of the SEF in the preceding fiscal year and the current year on the prescribed period; and

(e)	Municipal Accountant to improve its compliance in documenting claims with the necessary documents before payment to suppliers is made.

We recommended that management:

(a)	prepare and issue policy guidelines to address the necessity and propriety of hiring of job orders pursuant to Section 2, Rule XI of the Revised Omnibus on Appointments and Other Personnel Actions, Rules Implementing Book V of EO No. 292, in order to limit the expenditures to programs that are highly essential to merit the recruitment of the same; 

(b)	avoid the hiring of job orders whose functions overlap/duplicate with those of the regular employees of the Municipality; 

(c)	review the daily rates granted to job orders which should be commensurate to the nature of work assigned them; and 

(d)	ensure that the Statement of Duties and Responsibilities are stipulated in the contract of service in order to match their skills against the work to be performed.

We recommended that management:

(a)	institute necessary control in the issuance of fuel to all of its government owned motor service vehicles in order to abate possible wastage caused by unofficial trips.;

(b)	instruct personnel in charge to attach properly and fully accomplished driver’s trip tickets by supplying all data called for therein and the Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption and Monthly Report of Officials Travels as required in the Government Accounting and Auditing Manual be submitted for proper monitoring and control;

(c)	see to it that under no circumstances should fuel be issued to privately owned motor vehicles. No reimbursement for the cost of gasoline or diesel fuel and oil shall be drawn where a private vehicle is used; and

(d)	require the immediate settlement of the disallowed amount of ₱192,868.18 from all the persons liable.

